page.title: 15IMPRESSIONS OF DENTON
page.content:
First we went to the{railway}near the {canal}and we heard birds making tunes, planes humming,a jeep, rustling trees, guns firing and passing tains and cars. We saw a jeep, a factory, chimneys, smoke, train signals, a dead mouse, pylons,sheep, cows, a boy with his bike, three trains and the bridge, crossing the disused canal. By the canal we could see trees, a pond, horses, grass, seeds, birds, wild roses, a blackbird and a footpath. The flag of the{National Sea Training {College}was also visible. By the {Thames}we could see seagulls, a donkey, a helicopter, a cargo ship, stones, seaweed and driftwood. There was a jetty, a rowing boat and rocks.
{KARL SEAGER (9) { }
